(sign: ₹; code: inr) (रुपया — rupaya in hindi and similarly named in most indian languages, but taka in maithili and taakaa in bengali and toka in assamese). the rupee is subdivided into 100 paise (singular: paisa). 5 rupees 75 paise would normally be written as ₹5.75. common notes come in denominations of ₹5 (green), ₹10 (orange), ₹20 (red), ₹50 (purple), ₹100 (blue), ₹500 (yellow) and ₹1,000 (pink). it is always good to have a number of small notes on hand, as merchants and drivers sometimes have no change. a useful technique is to keep small notes (₹10-50) in your 